name: Aegean
description: Native to the Greek islands known as the Cyclades in the Aegean Sea, these are natural cats, meaning they developed without humans getting involved in their breeding. As a breed, Aegean Cats are rare, although they are numerous on their home islands. They are generally friendly toward people and can be excellent cats for families with children.

name: Abyssinian
description: The Abyssinian is athletic, agile, and playful, with a distinctive ticked coat. They are known for their curiosity and love of exploring.

name: American Bobtail
description: American Bobtails are known for their short, naturally bobbed tails and dog-like personalities. They are friendly and enjoy playing fetch.

name: American Shorthair
description: American Shorthairs are a classic breed known for their easygoing personalities and sturdy build. They are good with children and other pets.

name: Balinese
description: Balinese cats are essentially long-haired Siamese cats. They are known for their striking blue eyes, silky coats, and talkative nature.

name: Bengal
description: Bengals are a hybrid breed with a wild appearance due to their leopard-like spotted coats. They are active and enjoy interactive play.
